{"text": "Not this even dose the wicked-souled son of Dhritarashtra grant, thinking the proprietary rights of the entire earth to be vested in him. What is there more regrettable than this.", "meta": {"unique_id": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA_1_1", "parva_name": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA", "chapter": "1", "sentence": "1"}, "entities": [{"start_offset": 0, "end_offset": 13, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 14, "end_offset": 17, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 19, "end_offset": 32, "label": "OBJECT"}, {"start_offset": 21, "end_offset": 26, "label": "OBJECT"}, {"start_offset": 24, "end_offset": 29, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 27, "end_offset": 38, "label": "OBJECT"}, {"start_offset": 30, "end_offset": 36, "label": "OBJECT"}, {"start_offset": 33, "end_offset": 39, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 36, "end_offset": 38, "label": "SPATIAL"}, {"start_offset": 38, "end_offset": 49, "label": "EVENT"}], "relations": []}
{"text": "Having lost their arms and necks and having appeared like Kabandhas (a sort of headless ghosts), the Danavas fell (down into the sea) with fearful cries.", "meta": {"unique_id": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA_1_2", "parva_name": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA", "chapter": "1", "sentence": "2"}, "entities": [{"start_offset": 0, "end_offset": 7, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 14, "end_offset": 18, "label": "OBJECT"}, {"start_offset": 17, "end_offset": 22, "label": "OBJECT"}, {"start_offset": 19, "end_offset": 27, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 21, "end_offset": 25, "label": "SPATIAL_RELATION"}, {"start_offset": 23, "end_offset": 32, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 26, "end_offset": 31, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 29, "end_offset": 34, "label": "EVENT"}], "relations": [{"entity1": "Danavas", "relation": "FALLED_DOWN_TO", "entity2": "SEA"}, {"entity1": "Danavas", "relation": "FALLED_DOWN_TO", "entity2": "SEA"}]}
{"text": "“This (child) will be the west of men and the foremost of all the virtuous. He will be truthful and (also) greatly powerful; he will be the ruler of the earth.", "meta": {"unique_id": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA_1_3", "parva_name": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA", "chapter": "1", "sentence": "3"}, "entities": [{"start_offset": 0, "end_offset": 5, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 5, "end_offset": 9, "label": "LOCATION"}, {"start_offset": 8, "end_offset": 11, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 11, "end_offset": 19, "label": "CONCEPT"}, {"start_offset": 14, "end_offset": 22, "label": "CONCEPT"}, {"start_offset": 17, "end_offset": 24, "label": "CONCEPT"}, {"start_offset": 20, "end_offset": 28, "label": "CONCEPT"}, {"start_offset": 23, "end_offset": 28, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 26, "end_offset": 31, "label": "LOCATION"}], "relations": [{"entity1": "child", "relation": "TEACHER_OF", "entity2": "men"}]}
{"text": "Vaishampayana said Having heard these words of Vasudeva, all the kings assembled there, began to reproach the Chedi King.", "meta": {"unique_id": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA_1_4", "parva_name": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA", "chapter": "1", "sentence": "4"}, "entities": [{"start_offset": 0, "end_offset": 13, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 11, "end_offset": 21, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 16, "end_offset": 24, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 22, "end_offset": 25, "label": "CONCEPT"}, {"start_offset": 24, "end_offset": 29, "label": "CONCEPT"}, {"start_offset": 26, "end_offset": 35, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 28, "end_offset": 33, "label": "LOCATION"}, {"start_offset": 30, "end_offset": 35, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 32, "end_offset": 34, "label": "CONCEPT"}, {"start_offset": 34, "end_offset": 42, "label": "EVENT"}], "relations": []}
{"text": "O worshipful ascetic, I have intended to celebrate the sacrifice which you did propose to me once on a previous occasion, according to your instructions, and I now wish to appoint you, as officiating pricst at this sacrifice, the materials whereof I have collected, O excellent one, you are our family-priest, therefore do you take those sacrificial things and celebrate the sacrifice yourself.", "meta": {"unique_id": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA_1_5", "parva_name": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA", "chapter": "1", "sentence": "5"}, "entities": [{"start_offset": 0, "end_offset": 20, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 6, "end_offset": 7, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 10, "end_offset": 19, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 20, "end_offset": 23, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 25, "end_offset": 27, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 30, "end_offset": 39, "label": "ACTION"}, {"start_offset": 35, "end_offset": 39, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 40, "end_offset": 52, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 45, "end_offset": 46, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 50, "end_offset": 54, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 55, "end_offset": 62, "label": "ACTION"}], "relations": []}
{"text": "O descendant of Bharata's race! walking with hasty steps up and down, Nala obtained, near the inn, an excellent unsheathed sword.", "meta": {"unique_id": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA_1_6", "parva_name": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA", "chapter": "1", "sentence": "6"}, "entities": [{"start_offset": 0, "end_offset": 7, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 7, "end_offset": 11, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 13, "end_offset": 18, "label": "OBJECT"}, {"start_offset": 16, "end_offset": 19, "label": "LOCATION"}, {"start_offset": 19, "end_offset": 23, "label": "CONCEPT"}, {"start_offset": 22, "end_offset": 32, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 25, "end_offset": 30, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 28, "end_offset": 30, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 31, "end_offset": 35, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 34, "end_offset": 38, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 39, "end_offset": 47, "label": "EVENT"}], "relations": []}
{"text": "Is that declaration about satisfying all duties together due only to what is laid down by the great Rishis in days of yore, or does it refer to the duty of procreating children from religious motives, or has it reference to only the carnal pleasure that is expected from such an intercourse of the sexes?", "meta": {"unique_id": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA_1_7", "parva_name": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA", "chapter": "1", "sentence": "7"}, "entities": [{"start_offset": 0, "end_offset": 2, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 3, "end_offset": 7, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 6, "end_offset": 17, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 15, "end_offset": 20, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 19, "end_offset": 29, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 24, "end_offset": 27, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 27, "end_offset": 33, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 32, "end_offset": 40, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 36, "end_offset": 39, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 41, "end_offset": 45, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 45, "end_offset": 47, "label": "EVENT"}], "relations": []}
{"text": "Many kings have been kept imprisoned in Girivraja(his city), as dead carcasses of elephants are kept in the cave of a great mountains by the lion.", "meta": {"unique_id": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA_1_8", "parva_name": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA", "chapter": "1", "sentence": "8"}, "entities": [{"start_offset": 24, "end_offset": 33, "label": "LOCATION"}, {"start_offset": 31, "end_offset": 39, "label": "OBJECT"}, {"start_offset": 37, "end_offset": 41, "label": "OBJECT"}, {"start_offset": 41, "end_offset": 50, "label": "LOCATION"}, {"start_offset": 45, "end_offset": 49, "label": "CONCEPT"}, {"start_offset": 47, "end_offset": 54, "label": "OBJECT"}, {"start_offset": 50, "end_offset": 54, "label": "LOCATION"}, {"start_offset": 55, "end_offset": 59, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 61, "end_offset": 71, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 65, "end_offset": 69, "label": "CONCEPT"}, {"start_offset": 67, "end_offset": 74, "label": "OBJECT"}], "relations": []}
{"text": "The celestials accept the offerings of such a man on the expiration of a full year. His departed Manes also, when the time comes for him for performing the Shraddha, become pleased with him.", "meta": {"unique_id": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA_1_9", "parva_name": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA", "chapter": "1", "sentence": "9"}, "entities": [{"start_offset": 0, "end_offset": 10, "label": "OBJECT"}, {"start_offset": 7, "end_offset": 16, "label": "OBJECT"}, {"start_offset": 13, "end_offset": 18, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 17, "end_offset": 25, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 20, "end_offset": 25, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 23, "end_offset": 28, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 26, "end_offset": 31, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 29, "end_offset": 34, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 32, "end_offset": 37, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 35, "end_offset": 40, "label": "CHARACTER"}], "relations": []}
{"text": "Holding your behest on my head, I will, O lord, proceed piercing this impenetrable army, for rendering help, O best of men, to that son of Pandu.", "meta": {"unique_id": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA_1_10", "parva_name": "ANUKRAMANIKA PARVA", "chapter": "1", "sentence": "10"}, "entities": [{"start_offset": 0, "end_offset": 7, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 5, "end_offset": 7, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 7, "end_offset": 11, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 10, "end_offset": 18, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 14, "end_offset": 26, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 19, "end_offset": 23, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 24, "end_offset": 33, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 29, "end_offset": 33, "label": "EVENT"}, {"start_offset": 34, "end_offset": 38, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 38, "end_offset": 41, "label": "CHARACTER"}, {"start_offset": 44, "end_offset": 47, "label": "CHARACTER"}], "relations": []}
